4) Optional Class (VERY Important)

Optional class is container object used to avoid NullPointerException.
It helps when value may be null.

Difference between of(), ofNullable(), empty()?

✅ Answer:
Optional.of(value) → throws NullPointerException if value is null
Optional.ofNullable(value) → safe even if value is null
Optional.empty() → returns empty optional

   Optional<String> a = Optional.ofNullable(null); // OK
// Optional<String> b = Optional.of(null); // ❌ NPE

