✅ 7) Reflection API (Simple)
✅ What is Reflection?

Reflection means:
👉 Java can get class details at runtime
like:

class name
methods
fields

Used in frameworks like:
✅ Spring
✅ Hibernate

✅ Reflection Example (basic)
class Student {
    public void show() {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s = new Student();

        Class c = s.getClass();  // reflection
        System.out.println("Class Name: " + c.getName());
    }
}
